section.t:
 
   
Network operators who only wish to filter traffic originating from addresses that
should never be routed across the Internet can deploy a set of ingress filters 
designed to block traffic from address blocks reserved for special purposes. These 
are:

   
      
       - 0.0.0.0/8 (Local identification) ;
       - 10.0.0.0/8 (Private use) ;
       - 127.0.0.0/8 (Loopback) ; 
       - 169.254.0.0/16 (Link local) ; 
       - 172.16.0.0/12 (Private use) ;
       - 192.0.2.0/24 (TEST-NET-1) ; 
       - 192.168.0.0/16 (Private use) ; 
       - 198.18.0.0/15 (Benchmark testing) ;
       - 198.51.100.0/24 (TEST-NET-2) ;
       - 203.0.113.0/24 (TEST-NET-3) ;
       - 224.0.0.0/4 (Multicast) ; and
       - 240.0.0.0/4 (Future use) .
